2004_November 8 
You are thrust into the action right away as people fight for survival
against the undead in Racoon City and it all looks really good. Most
impressive is the lack of rampant cgi effects or cgi monsters. I do
believe the one's with the tongues are the only totally cgi monsters in
the movie. The nemesis monster is done completely with makeup it seems
and makes me think maybe they could have made a Hulk using the same
technique. This one picks up where the last one left off as Alice finds
herself in the middle of a virtual war. The additions to the cast are
all welcome changes from the last movie as the person who plays Jill
Valentine both looks and acts like the character from the game. Scores
of undead are killed and various other monsters and enemies line the
path as we follow a group of survivors desperate to get out of the
sealed city. Kind of sad that this one is so good and it is based
